ActivityCommentText: THIS C5 STREAM HAS A GREAT RIPARIAN OVERSTORY, BUT NO REGENERATION OF WOODY SPECIES. FILAMENTOUS GREEN ALGAE GROWING ON COBBLE IN CHANNEL - BIG MAT 50 FT DOWNSTREAM.. Approved status: CATHERINE GULLO 22-NOV-16 12:00:00--- SAMPLE TAKEN: Migrated

SANTA CRUZ RIVER IS AT BASEFLOW, CLEAR WITH LOTS OF MACROPHYTES LIVING ON BANKS AND AGOSIA REDS AT MARGINS. APPEARS SAME AS LAST YEAR. RIPARIAN VEG STABILIZES BANKS AND FLOODPLAIN. MOSTLY COTTONWOOD- WILLOW. NO TAMARISK HERE. BANKS STABLE, NO EROSION. LOTS OF BARS WITHIN ACTIVE CHANNEL = OVERLOADING OF SEDIMENT AND POOR SCORES. SOME PFANKUCH AND PKC PARAMETERS. FEW C-W SAPLINGS ON BARS, MACROPHYTE BEDS LINE STREAM MARGINS BUT VERY FEW FINE (SILT/CLAY) SEDS. HABITAT 80% RUN WITH SAND AND GRAVELS = POOR BUG HABITAT. FEW COBBLES ON RIFFLES AND EDGE VEG = HABITAT FOR BUGS WHICH CONSIST OF 3 SPP. DRAGONFLIES, MAYFLIES, BEETLES. ALGAE = ALL CLADOPHORA, DIATOM COVER VISIBLE - BROWN BIOFILM. NO CRAYFISH. AGOSIA ABUNDANT. 1 LEOPARD FROG.. Approved status: PATTI SPINDLER 10-JUN-16 12:00:00--- SAMPLE TAKEN: Migrated

ActivityCommentText: Small stream (headwaters of SCR) classified as C6. Great condition, low flow but all samples were taken + scoring  completed.  Healthy plant community, Mostly silt in pebble count.--- SAMPLE TAKEN: Yes; Normal Flow

Sampled 500 m upstream from GPS  coord. no flowing perennial water anywhere.  This was the longest wetted segment.  Whole reach very shallow (<2") and mostly pooled except where one pool flowed down through rocks into another.  Also UDA camps/food stashes everywhere and 2 border patrol guys were looking for a group that was there/come through recently.  Told us to "hike at our own risk".  We weren't sure if we should even sample, but did an abbreviated survey, everything except pebble count, bugs, but could not collect bugs anyway.  Filled brown bottle (turbidity / H2O column chlorophyl) with smaller bottle b/c waster wasn't deep enough to submerge.  Metals collection bottles could not be filled the whole way.--- SAMPLE TAKEN: Yes; Normal Flow

ActivityCommentText:
Current flow conditions: Baseflow
Habitat conditions for bugs: only one riffle, mostly run, but great side veg/macrophytes.
Large woody debris jam mid-channel, stream flowing under. Wider pool on upstream side.
Cottonwood and some willows leafed out. Sycamores and other Willows dormant. 
Pollution source and stressors: Active grazing.
Which macroinvertebrates seen:  Mayflies, Caddisflies, Belostomatidae, Damselfies, Dragonfly, small hellgramite.
Number of individuals seen: 1-19
Crayfish seen or in sample: No
Approx. Duration of flow prior to bug sample date: No precip in last 4 weeks. 
European narrow grass lines right bank for 30% of channel (bunch grass), cottonwoods look healthy, no saplings (due to grazing). Large debris dam could alter channel in high flows events, but right bank well protected with cottonwoods. Dace present. Willow flycatcher x 2 mid reach.--- SAMPLE TAKEN: Yes; Normal Flow
